  "body": "<!--üíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíé\r\n\r\nHellooo! üòÑ \r\n\r\nTo help us tend to your issue faster, please search our currently open issues before submitting a new one.\r\nExisting issues often contain information about workarounds, resolution, or progress updates.\r\n\r\nüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíéüíé-->\r\n\r\n# üêû Bug Report\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nWhile running the tests with the `-race` option enabled, the run reported a data race in the builder's client tests.\r\n\r\n### Has this worked before in a previous version?\r\n\r\n<!-- Did this behavior use to work in the previous version? -->\r\n<!-- ‚úçÔ∏è--> Yes, the previous version in which this bug was not present was: ....\r\n\r\n## üî¨ Minimal Reproduction\r\n\r\nJump into the `api/client/builder/` folder and run the following command:\r\n```shell\r\ngo test ./... -v -race\r\n```\r\n\r\n## üî• Error\r\n\r\n[Here are the logs](https://pastebin.com/nsSywi27).\r\n\r\n## üåç  Your Environment\r\n\r\n**Operating System:**\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\n  <code>\r\nMacOS Monterey v12.4\r\n  </code>\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\n**What version of Prysm are you running? (Which release)**\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\n  <code>\r\nbranch develop\r\n  </code>\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\n**Anything else relevant (validator index / public key)?**\r\n\r\nThe issue is caused by a concurrent read / write in a variable [used by the tests here](https://github.com/prysmaticlabs/prysm/blob/7fd2c08be3a5662602697342c618066dfaecedca/api/client/builder/client_test.go#L139).\r\n\r\nA quick fix for this issue would be to update the test as following:\r\n\r\n```golang\r\nfunc TestClient_RegisterValidator_Over100Requests(t *testing.T) {\r\n\treqs := make([]*eth.SignedValidatorRegistrationV1, 301)\r\n\tfor i := 0; i < len(reqs); i++ {\r\n\t\treqs[i] = &eth.SignedValidatorRegistrationV1{\r\n\t\t\tMessage: &eth.ValidatorRegistrationV1{\r\n\t\t\t\tFeeRecipient: ezDecode(t, params.BeaconConfig().EthBurnAddressHex),\r\n\t\t\t\tGasLimit:     23,\r\n\t\t\t\tTimestamp:    42,\r\n\t\t\t\tPubkey:       []byte(fmt.Sprint(i)),\r\n\t\t\t},\r\n\t\t}\r\n\t}\r\n\r\n\tvar total int32\r\n\r\n\tctx := context.Background()\r\n\thc := &http.Client{\r\n\t\tTransport: roundtrip(func(r *http.Request) (*http.Response, error) {\r\n\t\t\tbody, err := io.ReadAll(r.Body)\r\n\t\t\trequire.NoError(t, r.Body.Close())\r\n\t\t\trequire.NoError(t, err)\r\n\r\n\t\t\trecvd := make([]*SignedValidatorRegistration, 0)\r\n\t\t\trequire.NoError(t, json.Unmarshal(body, &recvd))\r\n\t\t\tif len(recvd) > registerValidatorBatchLimit {\r\n\t\t\t\tt.Errorf(\"Number of requests (%d) exceeds limit (%d)\", len(recvd), registerValidatorBatchLimit)\r\n\t\t\t}\r\n\t\t\tatomic.AddInt32(&total, int32(len(recvd)))\r\n\t\t\t// total += len(recvd)\r\n\r\n\t\t\trequire.Equal(t, http.MethodPost, r.Method)\r\n\t\t\treturn &http.Response{\r\n\t\t\t\tStatusCode: http.StatusOK,\r\n\t\t\t\tBody:       io.NopCloser(bytes.NewBuffer(nil)),\r\n\t\t\t\tRequest:    r.Clone(ctx),\r\n\t\t\t}, nil\r\n\t\t}),\r\n\t}\r\n\tc := &Client{\r\n\t\thc:      hc,\r\n\t\tbaseURL: &url.URL{Host: \"localhost:3500\", Scheme: \"http\"},\r\n\t}\r\n\r\n\trequire.NoError(t, c.RegisterValidator(ctx, reqs))\r\n\trequire.Equal(t, int32(len(reqs)), total)\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nBy updating `total`'s value using an atomic counter, concurrent read/write will be prevented.\r\nThe last assertion also needs to be updated, as the `len()` method returns an int and `total`'s type would be changed to be a int32.",
